  "title": "Principal Consultant",
  "description": "<p><u>Key Responsibilities:</u></p><p>•⁠  ⁠Design, implement, and manage AWS cloud infrastructure using\nTerraform.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Develop and maintain CI/CD pipelines for seamless deployment and\nautomation.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Author playbooks, scripts, and workflows for infrastructure and\napplication orchestration.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Ensure compliance and security standards, particularly in\nGovernment Commercial Cloud (GCC & GCC+), and SHIP-HAT tools.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Utilize Jira and automated testing tools to track, manage, and\nimprove deployment processes.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Collaborate with development teams to enhance Cloud DevOps\npractices.</p><p><u>Requirements:</u></p><p>•⁠  ⁠Strong hands-on experience with AWS and Terraform.<br /><br />•⁠  ⁠Proven expertise in Cloud DevOps and modern infrastructure management.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Solid understanding of CI/CD methodologies and best practices.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Experience with workflow orchestration, scripting, and automation\npipelines.</p><p>•⁠  ⁠Practical knowledge of Jira and automated testing frameworks.</p><p></p>",
